cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image sequence segmentation. The use of a fully convolutional network and a recurrent neural network also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The non-rigid label propagation and exponentially weighted loss function may indicate that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of MR images suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
